parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the RPM meter jumps up and down
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
the vehicle only moves in reverse
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic brake system can cause the vehicle to brake unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the malfunction warning light is illuminated
the brakes are depressed without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety features to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the AEB system can cause the vehicle to brake unexpectedly or fail to brake in emergency situations, leading to accidents.
The malfunction of the brake sensor can cause the vehicle to fail to start or experience unexpected braking, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to run out of gas without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the keyless ignition system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates while driving
the check engine light comes on and flashes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause the vehicle to fail to start, or the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the brake lights do not work
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes multiple attempts to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front radar sensor malfunction can cause the automatic emergency braking (AEB) system to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front radar sensor warning light comes on
the vehicle fails to detect obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gas and Brake Pedal Design Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the gas and brake pedals can cause accidental acceleration, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when braking
the driver's foot may be on both the brake and gas pedals simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drive belt failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to operate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive belt snaps or breaks
the vehicle stalls or fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Windshield gasket failure can cause the windshield to come loose while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The windshield gasket starts to come off while driving
the windshield must be held in place by closing the window or using duct tape.
